        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/horseman/{size}/53073_2.png",
        "created_at": "2025-07-25T19:44:35.751Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hello all,<br>\nI recently got a Sonim XP5s. Its running Android, but not the standard Googled variety. The problem is that it lacks a touch screen. Myself, and several people I know, are trying to move away from smart phones for various reasons, and these sort of devices are ‚Äúdumb enough‚Äù that they suit our needs. But, the lack of touch screen has shown me that Signal Android doesn‚Äôt work well at all with a D-pad.</p>\n<p>It seems to me that there is a need for a signal app with support for devices lacking a touch screen. Android-based bar or flip phones are available for cheap, and considering that they are degoogled by default, it appears that they  are perfect for the privacy focused. Sure, <em>maybe</em> they aren‚Äôt as secure as a custom ROM, but at least they escape the drag-net style surveillance and gives those of us with a desire to ditch traditional smartphones an option.</p>\n<p>If anyone has an idea what options may be available for devices without touch support, please share. If anyone thinks its a worth while idea and unaware of workarounds, maybe a feature request is in order.</p>",
